# Firebase
# composeApp/google-services.json is tracked *on purpose*, but what is committed is a **dummy**
# placeholder (project budgetmaster-dummy): the google-services plugin needs a well-formed file
# for any clone or CI run to build, while the real project config stays on the developer's
# machine and is never committed. So: do not ignore it, and do not commit changes to it —
# `git update-index --skip-worktree composeApp/google-services.json` keeps a local real config
# from showing up as a pending change. The iOS config has no such constraint, so it is ignored:
iosApp/GoogleService-Info.plist

# Signing — never commit a keystore or its passwords
keystore.properties
*.jks
*.keystore

# Secrets
secrets.properties
.env

